Here's a `ProductDetailViewModel` using the MVVM Community Toolkit (included with .NET MAUI):

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

namespace YourApp.ViewModels;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isBusy;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        if (IsBusy) return;

        try
        {
            IsBusy = true;

            // Replace with your actual data service call
            await Task.Delay(500);

            Name = "Sample Product";
            Price = 29.99m;
            IsAvailable = true;
        }
        finally
        {
            IsBusy = false;
        }
    }
}
```

**How it works:**

- `[ObservableProperty]` — source-generates the public property with `INotifyPropertyChanged` support (e.g., `_name` → `Name`).
- `[RelayCommand]` — generates `LoadCommand` (an `IAsyncRelayCommand`) from the `LoadAsync` method.
- Bind in XAML with `{Binding Name}`, `{Binding Price}`, `{Binding LoadCommand}`, etc.

**XAML usage example:**

```xml
<Label Text="{Binding Name}" />
<Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='{0:C}'}" />
<Switch IsToggled="{Binding IsAvailable}" />
<Button Text="Load" Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
<ActivityIndicator IsRunning="{Binding IsBusy}" />
```

The toolkit's NuGet package (`CommunityToolkit.Mvvm`) is already referenced by default in .NET MAUI projects. If not, add it:

```
dotnet add package CommunityToolkit.Mvvm
```
